						<p>Since the last version, W3 Total Cache wants to add a line to robots.txt. When this line is added (disallow wp-cache), it will disallow Google Bot to load the minified CSS. </p>
<p>When this line is added to robots.txt, Google Search Console will give errors on the &#8216;Mobile usability&#8217;. The reason for this is that Google Bot will no longer have access to the CSS and therefor will say that &#8216;text is too small to read&#8217;, &#8216;elements are close to each other&#8217; and &#8216;content is wider than screen&#8217;.</p>
<p>I&#8217;ve manually removed the line from robots.txt but now I will get an error on the admin pages saying that I should change my robots.txt. Please reconsider disallowing wp-cache.</p>


